<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>4241</id>
    <title>Upload and link to full image setting toggle not working</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Under a sites settings (My Sites &gt; Choose Site &gt; Settings) there is a toggle to Upload and link to full image.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">The wording of this is a bit confusing and I'm not entirely sure what it is meant to do.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">### Expected behavior
My expected behavior is if the toggle is turned off when I upload an image to a blog post it would not link the image to the full image.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">### Actual behavior
Whether this is turned on or off (in the legacy editor or the visual editor) when I upload an image to a post it includes a link to the full image.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">### Steps to reproduce the behavior</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">- Visit My Sites and choose a site</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">- Click Settings</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.4">- Turn off Upload and link to full image</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.5">- Start a blog post and add an image</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.6">- In visual editor click image and choose to edit, it will include a link to the full image</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.7">- In legacy editor publish the post then come back to edit</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.8">- Shows code linking to the full image</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">##### Tested on Nexus 5, Android 6.0.1, WP Android version alpha-13</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
